SIMPLE: inwardly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inwardly
<hw>In"ward*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>inweardlice</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>In the inner parts; internally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let Benedick, like covered fire,⟦br⟧
Consume away in sighs, waste <qex>inwardly</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Toward the center; inward; <as>as, to curve
<ex>inwardly</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In the heart or mind; mentally; privately; secretly;
<as>as, he <ex>inwardly</ex> repines</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Intimately; thoroughly.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall desire to know him more <qex>inwardly</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>inward-moving</ent>⟦br⟧
